properties.description:
PREPARE TO LEAVE: St Mary (Tiaro) bushfire as at 1.15pm Wed 3 Feb      Bushfire warning level: WATCH AND ACT     Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) advises there is a bushfire in St Mary, west of Tiaro, and conditions could get worse.    You need to be ready to follow your bushfire survival plan. If you do not have a plan, or intend to leave, you should be ready to leave the area because the situation could get worse quickly.    Currently as at 1.15pm, a dangerous fire is travelling from Glenbar Road towards St Mary State Forest. The fire is likely to impact St Mary.    Fire crews are working to contain the fire but firefighters may not be able to protect every property. You should not expect a firefighter at your door.    People in the area will be affected by smoke, which will reduce visibility and air quality.    Call Triple Zero (000) immediately if you believe your property is under threat. 
Response Time: 20210203105343
